(1) A member shall hold office for a period of three years and shall be eligible for re-appointment but shall not hold office for more than two terms.
A member shall hold office for a period of three years and shall be eligible for re-appointment but shall not hold office for more than two terms.
(2) Any member referred to in paragraph (a) of subsection (1) of section four may resign upon giving one month's notice in writing to the Minister and may be removed by the Minister at any time.
